FBIS4-57732 "drlat100_k_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-100 Daily Report 23 May 1994 SOUTH AMERICA Argentina UCR Leader Rejects Project UCR Leader Rejects Project PY2305200294 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 1730 GMT 23 May 94 PY2305200294 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS Spanish BFN [Text] Buenos Aires, 23 May (NA) -- UCR [Radical Civic Union] Party President Raul Alfonsin has confirmed his rejection of a government project to establish a security secretariat. He believes this proposal "is at odds with a full state of law." In a communique, the former Argentine president emphasized: "To establish this new government organization, it would be necessary to change basic laws." He asked the government "to maintain a responsible attitude, in keeping with our country's situation."
